1 April 2014 Minister of Arts and Culture, Paul Mashatile and Minister of Performance Monitoring and Evaluation, Collins Chabane will launch Freedom Month on Thursday, 3 April 2014 at Government Communication and Information System (GCIS). The theme for the 2014 Freedom Month celebrations is South Africa - a Better Place to live in. As part of the launch GCIS will host the National Communication Partnership to ensure that an inclusive information sharing platform is made available to all sectors of society. Rrepresentatives from business, labour, civil society, academia and media will attend the event for a shared vision in celebrating 20 years of Freedom.Participants will debate the following topics: 20 Years: An assessment of business opportunities in the last 20 years, Social Cohesion: How Far We Have Come! South Africa has a good story to tell, and 20 years: Media &amp; Marketing Plans.Media are invited as follows:Date: Thursday, 3 April 2014 Time: 09h00 Venue: GCIS, Tshedimosetso House, 1035 Frances Baard Street, Hatfield, PretoriaPROGRAMMEPART 1: Freedom Month Launch09h00 Arrival and registration 09h50 Speech by Minister Paul Mashatile 10h20 Photo OpportunityPART 2: National Communication Partnership11h00 -16h00 Panel discussionsMedia are requested to RSVP for both events to Ireen@gcis.gov.za/ 072 822 5869 or tshegofatso@gcis.gov.za/ 083 276 0786For more information on Twenty Years of Freedom events follow twitter updates on @20_YOFEnquiries: Nebo Legoabe Cell: 082 453 2874Issued by Government Communications and Information System (GCIS)